members.description:
Connects the Producer to its target destination. When a connection is established the <code>connected</code> property will change to <code>true</code> and this property is bindable and generates <code>PropertyChangeEvent</code>s. The internal TRIGGER_CONNECT_OPERATION CommandMessage that is sent will result in an acknowledge or fault event depending upon whether the underlying channel establishes its connection.   <pre>
 var producer:Producer = new Producer();
 producer.destination = &quot;TestTopic&quot;;
 producer.addEventListener(PropertyChangeEvent.PROPERTY_CHANGE, handleConnect);
 producer.connect();
 </pre>

Sends the specified message to its destination. If the producer is being used for publish/subscribe messaging, only messages of type AsyncMessage should be sent unless a custom message type is being used and the message destination on the server has been configured to process the custom message type.    <pre>
 var producer:Producer = new Producer();
 producer.destination = &quot;TestTopic&quot;;
 var msg:AsyncMessage = new AsyncMessage();
 msg.body = &quot;test message&quot;;
 producer.send(msg);
 </pre>
